cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the challenges and open research directions in systems, architectures, and security for AI. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions methodological advances in machine learning, which suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The discussion of the need for AI systems to make safe decisions in unpredictable environments and be robust against sophisticated adversaries suggests it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The mention of the need for confidentiality in processing increasing amounts of data suggests it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes open research directions in security, which suggests it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
